#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:1
msgid "E4087"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:3
msgid "Mutating something immutable, such as variable or struct field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:5
msgid ""
"MoonBit requires programmers to explicitly declare mutable variables and "
"struct fields. Notice that in MoonBit, mutability of variable only refers"
" to the variable itself, not the value it holds. So when you declare an "
"immutable `let` value of type `Array[T]`, `Ref[T]`, and `struct` with "
"mutable field, you can still mutate the inner structure, but cannot "
"replace the value of the whole variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:11
msgid ""
"Tuples are always immutable. If you want mutability, use a `struct` with "
"mutable field instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:13
msgid "Erroneous Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:15
msgid ""
"test {\n"
"  let a = @ref.new(0)\n"
"  a = @ref.new(1) // Error: The variable a is not mutable.\n"
"  a.val = 1 // This is valid, because the mutability come from `Ref` type"
" itself\n"
"  println(a)\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"struct S {\n"
"  x : Int\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"test {\n"
"  let s = { x: 1 }\n"
"  s.x = 2 // Error: The field `x` is not mutable.\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:33
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:35
msgid ""
"To fix this error, you need to declare the variable as mutable by adding "
"the `mut` keyword before the variable name or struct field name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4087.md:38
msgid ""
"test {\n"
"  let mut a = 0\n"
"  a = 1\n"
"  println(a)\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"struct S {\n"
"  mut x : Int\n"
"//^^^\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"test {\n"
"  let s = { x: 1 }\n"
"  s.x = 2\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

